---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { OODADiagram } from "../../components/blog/OODADiagram";
import { StatGrid } from "../../components/blog/StatGrid";

const title = "What Ukraine's Drones Taught Me About Building AI Systems";
const description =
  "Extracting software architecture lessons from autonomous drone systems, OODA loops, and distributed state management.";
const pubDate = new Date("2025-12-30");
const tags = ["ooda", "architecture", "multi-agent", "distributed-systems"];
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-20 overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
    <nav class="mb-12 animate-fade-in">
      <a
        href={`${base}blog`}
        class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 hover:text-copper transition-colors flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium group"
      >
        <svg
          class="w-4 h-4 transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            stroke-width="2"
            d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path>
        </svg>
        Back to Blog
      </a>
    </nav>

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-16">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6 animate-fade-in">
        {
          tags.map((tag) => (
            <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-copper/10 text-copper text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-copper/10">
              {tag}
            </span>
          ))
        }
      </div>

      <h1
        class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-6 leading-tight animate-slide-up"
      >
        What Ukraine's Drones <span class="text-copper">Taught Me</span> About Building
        AI Systems
      </h1>

      <p
        class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-8 border-l-4 border-copper pl-6 italic animate-slide-up animation-delay-100"
      >
        {description}
      </p>

      <div
        class="flex items-center gap-4 text-stone-500 font-medium animate-fade-in animation-delay-200"
      >
        <div
          class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700 flex items-center justify-center text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 font-bold border-2 border-white dark:border-stone-800 shadow-sm"
        >
          V
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-200 leading-none mb-1">
            Vario <span class="text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 font-normal">aka</span> <span class="text-copper font-normal">Mnehmos</span>
          </div>
          <time datetime={pubDate.toISOString()} class="text-sm">
            {
              pubDate.toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
                year: "numeric",
                month: "long",
                day: "numeric",
              })
            }
          </time>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Content Hook: Uncomfortable Disclaimer -->
    <div
      class="bg-stone-900 text-stone-300 p-8 rounded-3xl mb-16 relative overflow-hidden group animate-fade-in hover:shadow-2xl transition-shadow border border-white/10"
    >
      <div
        class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-4 opacity-20 pointer-events-none group-hover:opacity-40 transition-opacity"
      >
        <svg class="w-32 h-32" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          ><path
            d="M12 2L1 21h22L12 2zm0 3.45L19.15 19H4.85L12 5.45zM11 16h2v2h-2v-2zm0-7h2v5h-2V9z"
          ></path></svg
        >
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-copper">!</span> A Note on Context
      </h3>
      <p class="relative z-10 leading-relaxed">
        The most sophisticated AI deployment in the world right now isn't in
        Silicon Valley. It's on a 600-mile front line in Ukraine. I'm about to
        extract software architecture lessons from weapons systems—systems
        designed to kill people. I don't want to sanitize their origin, nor do I
        want to celebrate it. This is an attempt to learn from necessity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Section: The Problem -->
    <section
      class="prose prose-stone dark:prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none mb-20 scroll-reveal"
    >
      <h2 class="font-display text-copper text-3xl font-bold mb-6">
        The Problem: Manual Drones Were Failing
      </h2>
      <p>
        By mid-2024, the situation for Ukrainian drone operators had changed
        dramatically. Russian electronic warfare (EW) had improved to the point
        where manual FPV drone hit rates dropped to <strong>30-50%</strong> under
        jamming. For new pilots, it was as low as <strong>10%</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The solution wasn't better pilots or stronger signals. It was rethinking
        the <strong>latency of the decision loop</strong>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- OODA Component -->
    <div class="mb-20 scroll-reveal">
      <h2
        class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-8 text-center uppercase tracking-widest"
      >
        The OODA Framework
      </h2>
      <OODADiagram client:visible />
    </div>

    <!-- Section: DELTA -->
    <section class="mb-20 scroll-reveal">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-900 border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 p-8 md:p-12 rounded-4xl shadow-sm relative overflow-hidden transition-colors"
      >
        <div
          class="absolute -right-20 -top-20 w-64 h-64 bg-copper/5 rounded-full blur-3xl"
        >
        </div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-copper text-4xl font-bold mb-4">
          DELTA: The OS of the Battlefield
        </h2>
        <p
          class="text-lg text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed"
        >
          DELTA is Ukraine’s Situational Awareness and Battlefield Management
          System. It's a cloud-native platform that aggregates data from
          thousands of sensors—drones, satellites, chatbots, and signal
          intelligence—into a single interface.
        </p>

        <StatGrid client:visible />

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-12">
          <div
            class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-950 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-stone-100 dark:border-stone-800 h-full transition-all hover:border-copper/30 group"
          >
            <h4
              class="font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"
            >
              <span
                class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-copper/10 text-copper flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-mono transition-transform group-hover:scale-110"
                >01</span
              >
              Observe & Orient
            </h4>
            <p
              class="text-sm text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
              The aggregate stream of thousands of drones is processed by <strong
                >Vezha</strong
              > and <strong>Avengers AI</strong>, identifying over 12,000 enemy
              units per week automatically.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-950 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-stone-100 dark:border-stone-800 h-full transition-all hover:border-copper/30 group"
          >
            <h4
              class="font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"
            >
              <span
                class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-copper/10 text-copper flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-mono transition-transform group-hover:scale-110"
                >02</span
              >
              Decide & Act
            </h4>
            <p
              class="text-sm text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
              The <strong>TFL-1 terminal guidance module</strong> ($50-$100) handles
              the "last mile." Once the operator selects a target, the drone locks
              on and strikes autonomously, even if the radio link is severed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section: DELTA Deep Dive -->
    <section
      class="prose prose-stone dark:prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none mb-20 scroll-reveal"
    >
      <h2 class="font-display text-copper text-3xl font-bold mb-6">
        DELTA: OODA at National Scale
      </h2>
      <p>
        DELTA is Ukraine's situational awareness and battlefield management
        system. According to CSIS analysis and Ukrainian government statements,
        it aggregates data from drones, satellites, ground sensors, radar, and
        even civilian informants via chatbots—all into a single interface that
        runs on standard laptops, tablets, and phones.
      </p>

      <p>
        What matters architecturally: DELTA is built as an ecosystem of modules,
        each handling a different phase of the OODA loop.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-12 not-prose">
        <div
          class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-copper"
        >
          <h3
            class="font-display font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
          >
            OBSERVE
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Drone video feeds via Vezha
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Satellite imagery integration
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Ground sensor networks
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Civilian intelligence chatbots
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-copper"
        >
          <h3
            class="font-display font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
          >
            ORIENT
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Avengers AI analyzes video
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Identifies 70% of enemy units
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Detection time: ~2.2s per unit
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Automatic feed prioritization
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-copper"
        >
          <h3
            class="font-display font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
          >
            DECIDE
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Deltamonitor live map
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Target Hub prioritizes strikes
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Direct digital mission assignment
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> "Uber for Artillery" routing
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-copper"
        >
          <h3
            class="font-display font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
          >
            ACT
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Mission Control coordination
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> AI terminal guidance (TFL-1)
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Automated result feedback
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-copper mt-1">▪</span> Rapid re-looping
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        In December 2024, Ukrainian forces reportedly conducted their first
        fully unmanned operation near Lyptsi—reconnaissance, target acquisition,
        and strike executed by machines with human oversight but not direct
        control.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Nervous System Insight -->
    <section class="mb-20 scroll-reveal">
      <div
        class="relative bg-stone-900 rounded-4xl p-8 md:p-12 overflow-hidden text-stone-300"
      >
        <div
          class="absolute inset-0 bg-linear-to-b from-stone-800/50 to-stone-900 pointer-events-none"
        >
        </div>
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-10">
          <svg class="w-64 h-64" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
            <path
              d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm-1 14H9V8h2v8zm4 0h-2V8h2v8z"
            ></path>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="relative z-10">
          <h2
            class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-6"
          >
            The Nervous System Insight
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">
            Here's what changed my thinking about AI architecture: <strong
              >safety features need to operate at nervous system speed.</strong
            >
          </p>
          <p class="mb-8">
            When you touch something hot, you don't think "that's hot, I should
            move my hand." Your hand is already moving. The reflex happens
            before conscious processing.
          </p>

          <div
            class="bg-black/50 rounded-xl p-6 font-mono text-sm border border-white/10 mb-8 overflow-x-auto"
          >
            <pre class="text-blue-300">LAYER 1: REFLEXES (milliseconds)</pre>
            ├── Hardcoded limits ├── Immediate fallbacks ├── Circuit breakers └──
            No AI involved—just rules

            <pre class="text-blue-300 mt-4">LAYER 2: REACTIONS (seconds)</pre>
            ├── Pattern matching (machine vision) ├── Known-good responses └── Lightweight
            inference

            <pre
              class="text-blue-300 mt-4">LAYER 3: REASONING (seconds to minutes)</pre>
            ├── Full situational analysis ├── Complex planning └── Human decision
            points
          </div>

          <p class="mb-8">
            Most AI systems put everything in Layer 3. That's like routing "hand
            on stove" through your prefrontal cortex. You'll figure out the
            right answer eventually—with burns.
          </p>

          <p class="mb-6">
            I learned this the hard way. Early versions of my RPG game engine
            let the AI agent manage character hit points directly. Prompt
            instructions said "never reduce HP below zero." Worked fine in
            testing. In production, a complex sequence blew right past it.
          </p>

          <p class="mb-4">
            The fix wasn't better prompting. It was moving the constraint to
            code:
          </p>

          <div
            class="bg-stone-950 rounded-xl p-6 font-mono text-sm border-l-4 border-copper text-stone-300 overflow-x-auto"
          >
            <code class="block font-mono">
              <span class="text-stone-500"
                >// This runs AFTER the agent acts, BEFORE state commits</span
              ><br />
              <span class="text-purple-400">if</span> (character.hp &lt; <span
                class="text-orange-400">0</span
              >) character.hp = <span class="text-orange-400">0</span>;<br />
              <span class="text-purple-400">if</span> (character.hp === <span
                class="text-orange-400">0</span
              > && !character.deathSavesStarted) &#123;<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;character.deathSavesStarted = <span
                class="text-blue-400">true</span
              >;<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="text-yellow-300">emit</span>(<span
                class="text-green-300">'death_save_required'</span
              >, character.id);<br />
              &#125;
            </code>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-stone-500 italic">
            The agent can't reason its way around this. It's not a suggestion.
            It's a reflex.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Database Intelligence -->
    <section
      class="prose prose-stone dark:prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none mb-20 scroll-reveal"
    >
      <h2 class="font-display text-copper text-3xl font-bold mb-6">
        The Database Is the Intelligence
      </h2>
      <p>
        Another insight: <strong
          >the agent isn't smart. The database is smart. The agent is just
          hands.</strong
        >
      </p>
      <p>
        Ukraine's "mother drone" system illustrates this. A carrier drone
        delivers AI-guided FPVs 300km behind enemy lines. The AI doesn't "know"
        anything substantial. It queries onboard models and sensor data. Kill
        the process, spin up a new one, feed it the same data—same output.
      </p>

      <div class="my-12 not-prose">
        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-800 border-2 border-stone-900 dark:border-stone-700 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 font-mono text-sm md:text-base shadow-[8px_8px_0px_0px_rgba(28,25,23,1)] dark:shadow-[8px_8px_0px_0px_rgba(255,255,255,0.1)] transition-colors"
        >
          <div
            class="border-b-2 border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-600 pb-4 mb-4 text-center font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
          >
            DATABASE (THE ACTUAL INTELLIGENCE)
          </div>
          <div class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-6 text-center">
            Sensor feeds • Drone telemetry • Target coordinates<br />
            Unit positions • Historical patterns
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-center mb-6">
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-stone-400 animate-bounce"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M19 14l-7 7m0 0l-7-7m7 7V3"></path></svg
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-900 rounded-lg p-4 text-stone-700 dark:text-stone-300"
          >
            <div
              class="font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-2 border-b border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-700 pb-2"
            >
              STATELESS PROCESSES
            </div>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Avengers:</span>
                <span class="text-stone-500">Video analysis</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Target Hub:</span>
                <span class="text-stone-500">Strike planning</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Vezha:</span>
                <span class="text-stone-500">Stream routing</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div
            class="mt-4 text-center text-xs text-stone-400 uppercase tracking-widest font-bold"
          >
            These are just automation
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        Lose a situational awareness center? The others keep running. Lose a
        drone operator's connection? The AI completes the strike. The system
        degrades gracefully because state lives in the database, not in any
        single process.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Architecture Lessons / Conclusion -->
    <section
      class="bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-900 rounded-4xl p-8 md:p-12 mb-20 scroll-reveal transition-colors"
    >
      <h2
        class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-8"
      >
        How This Shapes My Architecture
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 mb-8">
        I build MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers—the tools that let AI
        agents interact with the world. Every tool I build now follows these
        wartime lessons.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-950 p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3
            class="font-bold text-copper mb-2 uppercase tracking-wide text-sm"
          >
            Separation of Concerns
          </h3>
          <h4
            class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-4"
          >
            Split by OODA Phase
          </h4>
          <ul
            class="space-y-4 font-mono text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400"
          >
            <li
              class="p-3 bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-900 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-400"
            >
              <strong class="text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-200"
                >OBSERVE:</strong
              > Read-only tools (get_context, search_index)
            </li>
            <li
              class="p-3 bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-900 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-yellow-400"
            >
              <strong class="text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-200">ORIENT:</strong
              > Analysis tools (validate_schema, check_line_of_sight)
            </li>
            <li
              class="p-3 bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-900 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-purple-400"
            >
              <strong class="text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-200">DECIDE:</strong
              > The LLM reasons over observed + oriented data
            </li>
            <li
              class="p-3 bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-900 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-red-400"
            >
              <strong class="text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-200">ACT:</strong> Write
              tools with built-in reflexes (emit_event, execute_action)
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-950 p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3
            class="font-bold text-copper mb-2 uppercase tracking-wide text-sm"
          >
            Latency & Autonomy
          </h3>
          <h4
            class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-4"
          >
            What Centralizes vs. What stays Local?
          </h4>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <div
                class="font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-200 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-4 h-4 text-stone-400"
                  fill="none"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  ><path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4"
                  ></path></svg
                >
                Centralize
              </div>
              <ul
                class="text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 space-y-1 list-disc pl-4"
              >
                <li>Shared context</li>
                <li>Historical decisions</li>
                <li>Schema contracts</li>
                <li>Coordination state</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div
                class="font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-200 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2"
              >
                <svg
                  class="w-4 h-4 text-stone-400"
                  fill="none"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  ><path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M5 12h.01M12 12h.01M19 12h.01M6 12a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm7 0a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm7 0a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0z"
                  ></path></svg
                >
                Keep Local
              </div>
              <ul
